f raising children.<br>
<br>
So while governments, given their mission, have an interest in birth rate, =
the government would have to redefine cultural norms, and that is something=
 they are bad at. So I think the government could be helpful on one side of=
 the equation but not the other. It should be added that the United States,=
 as a rapidly growing economy, has frequently had the imperative to expand =
its population, something that has historically been solved by immigration =
=E2=80=93 no one but a Native Americans can claim not to descend from or be=
 migrants to the U.S. But migrants historically create social stresses whil=
